main.name: Jenny Shen
main.description: Faster learner and passionate about learning technology
main.bio: My name is Jenny, a recent graduate from the University of Queensland with a degree in Software Engineering. Experience in Python, C#, and TypeScript, I am passionate about creating innovative software solutions. I thrive on challenges and am eager to continue learning and growing in the field.

work.title: Backend developer Internship
description: • Design and implement an algorithm to retrieve the most recent reminder events over a specified time period, optimising performance and usability (Typescript)
• Use DynamoDB to store and manage the properties, reminders and users’ data
• Implemented API changes to enhance functionality and user experience, including modifying the `POST` and `GET` method to improve data retrieval efficiency
• Setup Backend by using Nodejs and deploy project into AWS
• Collaborate with front end developers to integrate backend functionalities and create user-friendly website

work.title: Research Assistant
description: • Utilised Python to train various password guessing models, explore enhancement of cybersecurity measures.
• Conducted several experiments to evaluate the performance of different models, focusing on the guessing ability in various scenarios.
• Analysed experimental data to identify key factors influencing model effectiveness, help to improve in model design and functionality.
• Wrote detailed research papers on the outcomes and findings of the experiments.
